en: R1886- Fish Bay Whale Channel Night Dive (2015 Dive 1)

Underwater video shot during a Leys Lab cruise in October 2015.

Dive plan: Calibrate, against Vector, two ThD, 10-11, 12-13. Calibrate one single, ThS 9. Pull three SIPs. Collect water for fluorescein, and recover all instruments. During calibration, search for Farrea sponges. Calibrate for at least 30 minutes.

Dive accomplishments: Deployed and calibrated ThD 10-11, 12-13, and ThS 9. Performed flyover for sponge pictures. Failed to deploy SIPs due to bungee cord issues. Collected water via Niskins for fluorescein. Failed to collect water via suction sampler- clogged? Recovered ThS-9. Deployed vector ADV. Failed to find Farrea sponges.
